tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE vehicle_performance_data (
  vehicle_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  acceleration FLOAT,
  speed FLOAT,
  battery_level FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE VehicleData (
    vehicle_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    acceleration FLOAT,
    speed FLOAT,
    temperature FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceData (
    maintenance_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id UUID,
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
    description TEXT,
    CONSTRAINT fk_vehicle_id FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES VehicleData(vehicle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE vehicle_data (
    vehicle_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    speed FLOAT,
    mileage FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    sensor_type VARCHAR(50),
    data_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE maintenance_log (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
    maintenance_date DATE,
    maintenance_details TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE sensor_data (
  sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  vehicle_id INT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  sensor_reading FLOAT,
  sensor_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE maintenance_events (
  event_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  vehicle_id INT,
  event_type VARCHAR(50),
  event_description TEXT,
  event_timestamp TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE Vehicle (
    vehicle_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    make VARCHAR(255),
    model VARCHAR(255),
    year INT,
    energy_type VARCHAR(50),
    last_maintenance_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE SensorData (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    sensor_type VARCHAR(50),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    data_value FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES Vehicle(vehicle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE MaintenanceSchedule (
    schedule_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    maintenance_type VARCHAR(50),
    scheduled_date DATE,
    completed BOOLEAN,
    FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES Vehicle(vehicle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE PerformanceMetrics (
    metric_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    metric_name VARCHAR(255),
    metric_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES Vehicle(vehicle_id)
);

CREATE TABLE EnergyEfficiency (
    efficiency_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_id INT,
    efficiency_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (vehicle_id) REFERENCES Vehicle(vehicle_id)
);
